docs.abstract: The Education Department failed to effectively manage its student loan collectors, a government audit said, increasing costs for borrowers and taxpayers.
docs.snippet: The Education Department failed to effectively manage its student loan collectors, a government audit said, increasing costs for borrowers and taxpayers.
docs.lead_paragraph: An audit released by the Education Department on Thursday described its slipshod oversight of federal student loan servicers that were regularly let off the hook for mistakes, driving up costs for taxpayers and for borrowers already owing more than $1 trillion in debt.

headline.main: Student Loan Servicers’ Frequent Mistakes Went Unpunished, Audit Finds
headline.print_headline: Audit Finds Lax Management of Student Loan Servicers

docs.abstract: Stormy times continue at the Pittsburgh daily, where the publisher and newsroom employees are at odds.
docs.snippet: Stormy times continue at the Pittsburgh daily, where the publisher and newsroom employees are at odds.
docs.lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — Last year, The Pittsburgh Post-Gazette chose Martin Luther King’s Birthday as the publication date for an editorial headlined “Reason as Racism.” On Monday, a little more than a year after that piece drew national criticism, The Post-Gazette named its editorial page director, Keith C. Burris, as its newsroom leader.

headline.main: Post-Gazette Appoints Writer of ‘Reason as Racism’ Editorial as Its Newsroom Leader
headline.print_headline: Pittsburgh Post-Gazette Names Editor to Lead A Divided Newsroom

docs.abstract: The Fed released minutes of its January meeting showing officials continued to express confidence in the economy but saw enough warning signs to warrant a pause in rate increases.
docs.snippet: The Fed released minutes of its January meeting showing officials continued to express confidence in the economy but saw enough warning signs to warrant a pause in rate increases.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal Reserve officials decided in late January to pause their steady campaign to raise interest rates as the global economic outlook became less certain and financial markets failed to appreciate the Fed’s willingness to shift if the economy weakened, according to the minutes of that meeting released on Wednesday.

headline.main: Fed Explains Pause as Officials Debate Future Rate Increases
headline.print_headline: Minutes Show Mixed Outlook  From Fed on Rate Increases

docs.abstract: Google said it had deleted the accounts and channels of people leaving the comments in question, but acknowledged “there’s more to be done.”
docs.snippet: Google said it had deleted the accounts and channels of people leaving the comments in question, but acknowledged “there’s more to be done.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Nestlé, Epic Games and other major brands said on Wednesday that they had stopped buying advertisements on YouTube after their ads appeared on children’s videos where pedophiles had infiltrated the comment sections.

headline.main: Advertisers Boycott YouTube After Pedophiles Swarm Comments on Videos of Children
headline.print_headline: Advertisers Flee YouTube Over Pedophiles’ Interest

docs.abstract: The battle over Amazon’s New York plans resurfaced tensions among unions over how to deal with Uber, Airbnb and other emerging giants.
